Another Kenyan international Francis Kahata also plays for Simba, but has not been featuring regularly in competitive matches and Onyango feels for him.“Vandenbroeck was a good coach and we had developed a good relationship before he left. We are also very close with Kahata and we have been encouraging each other, though in football sometimes one has to be down. Kachi (Kahata) will get back to his form and shine again,” says Onyango.   Harambee Stars defender Joash ‘Berlin Wall’ Onyango can't wait to make his debut in the Caf Champions League group stages with Tanzanian giants Simba SC.
The former Gor Mahia defender says this will be the perfect opportunity to showcase his talent and even attract interest from big clubs so as to achieve his dream of playing in Europe in the future.



